article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 75, Cent. Connecticut St. 67
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- Central Connecticut's Dave Simmons tied his career high with 16 points, but the Blue Devils' inability to score late helped Monmouth earn a 75-67 victory Thursday night. Will Campbell and Travis Taylor led Monmouth (8-22, 6-11 Northeast Conference) with 20 points each. The Hawks stayed alive in the race for the last NEC Tournament berth, while Central (13-15, 8-9 Northeast Conference) lost any hope it had of finishing in the top four and getting a home game in the first round. Trailing by seven midway through the second half, the Hawks came right back behind Campbell and Nick Deltufo, who sparked a 14-7 Hawks' surge capped by an Alex Nunner three that tied things at 60 with 4:57 left. Nunner's three with 2:18 left gave the Hawks their first lead of the night, 68-67. Central committed a pair of big turnovers late.
